<subSubSection id="C30175E2FFB9FFAAC6A451A5FCCAFCFC" pageId="13" pageNumber="214" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BA42669FFB9FFAAC6A451A5FD85FEE0" blockId="13.[151,1437,150,1113]" pageId="13" pageNumber="214">
<emphasis id="B96FFA7BFFB9FFAAC6A451A5FE9FFF10" bold="true" box="[151,274,150,176]" pageId="13" pageNumber="214">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Female. Apical seta longer than maximum width of palpus; fore tarsomere 5 a little longer than fore tarsomere 1; setal palisade 1/2 length of mid tibia; setulae below basal half of hind femur shorter than those of anteroventral row of outer half; tergite VI narrow, weakly sclerotized, each lateral quarter with 3 long and 5–6 shorter setulae; sternite VI divided into two pieces, with 2–3 long and 4–5 short setae; dorsum of oviscape with 12 short setulae on sub-apex of each side.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA42669FFB9FFAAC6F45079FABBFE54" blockId="13.[151,1437,150,1113]" pageId="13" pageNumber="214">
<emphasis id="B96FFA7BFFB9FFAAC6F45079FEA8FEC4" bold="true" box="[199,293,330,356]" pageId="13" pageNumber="214">Female.</emphasis>
Body length 
<quantity id="4CE38B8CFFB9FFAAC7F35079FDA5FEC5" box="[448,552,330,357]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.25" pageId="13" pageNumber="214" unit="mm" value="1.25">1.25 mm</quantity>
. Frons (
<figureCitation id="13203AECFFB9FFAAC4B05079FD51FEC4" box="[643,732,330,356]" captionStart="FIGURES 8" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1895,1919]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,697,1866]" captionTargetId="figure-169@12.[151,1435,697,1869]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 8A–G. Pseudacteon botulpalpatus Disney et Michailovskaya, female.A. head, anterior view; B. wing, dorsal view; C. fore tarsus, posterior view; D. mid tibia, posterior view; E. hind femur, anterior view; F. tergite VI and sternite VI; G. ovipositor, right view. Scale bar = 0.1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559553" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559553/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="214">Fig. 8A</figureCitation>
) brown, with 22–26 setulae. Supra-antennal setae as strong as adjacent frontal setae, upper pair slightly higher on frons than lower fronto-orbital setae. Lower interfrontal seta directly under fronto-orbital setae. Second row of frontal setae slightly concave, with lower interfrontal setae clearly further apart than either is from a lower fronto-orbital seta. Flagellomere 1 brown and subglobose. Palpus pale yellow, with 5 long setae, apical one longer than maximum width of palpus. Labrum and labella pale yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA42669FFB9FFAAC6F450CDFA18FD6C" blockId="13.[151,1437,150,1113]" pageId="13" pageNumber="214">
Thorax brown. Scutellum with two pairs of setae, posterior twice length of anterior. Legs yellowish brown to brown. Ratios of lengths of fore tarsomeres 0.93: 0.67: 0.66: 0.57: 1, with all five bearing a posterodorsal setal palisade (
<figureCitation id="13203AECFFB9FFAAC7305375FED1FDC0" box="[259,348,582,608]" captionStart="FIGURES 8" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1895,1919]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,697,1866]" captionTargetId="figure-169@12.[151,1435,697,1869]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 8A–G. Pseudacteon botulpalpatus Disney et Michailovskaya, female.A. head, anterior view; B. wing, dorsal view; C. fore tarsus, posterior view; D. mid tibia, posterior view; E. hind femur, anterior view; F. tergite VI and sternite VI; G. ovipositor, right view. Scale bar = 0.1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559553" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559553/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="214">Fig. 8C</figureCitation>
). Setal palisade 1/2 length of mid tibia (
<figureCitation id="13203AECFFB9FFAAC5125375FCF1FDC0" box="[801,892,582,608]" captionStart="FIGURES 8" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1895,1919]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,697,1866]" captionTargetId="figure-169@12.[151,1435,697,1869]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 8A–G. Pseudacteon botulpalpatus Disney et Michailovskaya, female.A. head, anterior view; B. wing, dorsal view; C. fore tarsus, posterior view; D. mid tibia, posterior view; E. hind femur, anterior view; F. tergite VI and sternite VI; G. ovipositor, right view. Scale bar = 0.1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559553" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559553/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="214">Fig. 8D</figureCitation>
). Setulae below basal half of hind femur shorter than those of anteroventral row of outer half (
<figureCitation id="13203AECFFB9FFAAC4A75359FD66FD24" box="[660,747,618,644]" captionStart="FIGURES 8" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1895,1919]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,697,1866]" captionTargetId="figure-169@12.[151,1435,697,1869]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 8A–G. Pseudacteon botulpalpatus Disney et Michailovskaya, female.A. head, anterior view; B. wing, dorsal view; C. fore tarsus, posterior view; D. mid tibia, posterior view; E. hind femur, anterior view; F. tergite VI and sternite VI; G. ovipositor, right view. Scale bar = 0.1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559553" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559553/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="214">Fig. 8E</figureCitation>
). Wing (
<figureCitation id="13203AECFFB9FFAAC5795359FC2DFD24" box="[842,928,618,644]" captionStart="FIGURES 8" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1895,1919]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,697,1866]" captionTargetId="figure-169@12.[151,1435,697,1869]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 8A–G. Pseudacteon botulpalpatus Disney et Michailovskaya, female.A. head, anterior view; B. wing, dorsal view; C. fore tarsus, posterior view; D. mid tibia, posterior view; E. hind femur, anterior view; F. tergite VI and sternite VI; G. ovipositor, right view. Scale bar = 0.1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559553" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559553/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="214">Fig. 8B</figureCitation>
) length 1.00– 
<quantity id="4CE38B8CFFB9FFAAC20F5359FB2CFD25" box="[1084,1185,618,645]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.02" pageId="13" pageNumber="214" unit="mm" value="1.02">1.02 mm</quantity>
, width 
<quantity id="4CE38B8CFFB9FFAAC2C05359FA15FD25" box="[1267,1432,618,645]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.75" metricValueMax="4.8" metricValueMin="4.699999999999999" pageId="13" pageNumber="214" unit="mm" value="0.475" valueMax="0.48" valueMin="0.47">0.47–0.48 mm</quantity>
, width/length 0.47. Costal index 0.37. Costal ratio 1.56: 1, second section with 4 dorsal setulae. Costal cilia 
<quantity id="4CE38B8CFFB9FFAAC37C53BDFE84FD6D" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.449999999999999" metricValueMax="4.5" metricValueMin="4.3999999999999995" pageId="13" pageNumber="214" unit="mm" value="0.0445" valueMax="0.045" valueMin="0.044">
<geoCoordinate id="EE2F40AEFFB9FFAAC37C53BDFA03FD08" box="[1359,1422,654,680]" degrees="0.044" direction="north" orientation="latitude" pageId="13" pageNumber="214" precision="55" value="0.044">0.044</geoCoordinate>
<geoCoordinate id="EE2F40AEFFB9FFAAC3BD53BDFF5BFD6D" degrees="0.045" direction="west" orientation="longitude" pageId="13" pageNumber="214" precision="55" value="-0.045">– 0.045</geoCoordinate>
mm
</quantity>
long. Alula with 2 setae. Veins brown, thin veins being paler. Membrane brownish gray. Haltere brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA42669FFB9FFAAC6F453E5FCCAFCFC" blockId="13.[151,1437,150,1113]" pageId="13" pageNumber="214">
Abdominal tergites brown and tergites I–V with sparse minute setulae only. Tergite VI reduced to a narrow transverse strip, bearing 3–4 long setae and 4–5 short setulae each side. Sternite VI divided into two oval pieces, each with 2 long setae (
<figureCitation id="13203AECFFB9FFAAC799522DFD8CFC98" box="[426,513,798,824]" captionStart="FIGURES 8" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1895,1919]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,697,1866]" captionTargetId="figure-169@12.[151,1435,697,1869]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 8A–G. Pseudacteon botulpalpatus Disney et Michailovskaya, female.A. head, anterior view; B. wing, dorsal view; C. fore tarsus, posterior view; D. mid tibia, posterior view; E. hind femur, anterior view; F. tergite VI and sternite VI; G. ovipositor, right view. Scale bar = 0.1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559553" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559553/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="214">Fig. 8F</figureCitation>
). Oviscape brown. The dorsum of the oviscape 3–4 small setulae each side. The venter of the oviscape with 6 fine setulae each side (
<figureCitation id="13203AECFFB9FFAAC4D35271FCB6FCFC" box="[736,827,834,860]" captionStart="FIGURES 8" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1895,1919]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,697,1866]" captionTargetId="figure-169@12.[151,1435,697,1869]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 8A–G. Pseudacteon botulpalpatus Disney et Michailovskaya, female.A. head, anterior view; B. wing, dorsal view; C. fore tarsus, posterior view; D. mid tibia, posterior view; E. hind femur, anterior view; F. tergite VI and sternite VI; G. ovipositor, right view. Scale bar = 0.1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559553" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559553/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="214">Fig. 8G</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C30175E2FFB9FFAAC6F45255FE97FC68" pageId="13" pageNumber="214" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BA42669FFB9FFAAC6F45255FDBCFC21" blockId="13.[151,1437,150,1113]" box="[199,561,870,897]" pageId="13" pageNumber="214">
