<subSubSection id="C30175E2FFB9FFAAC6F452E1FC85FBF8" pageId="13" pageNumber="214" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BA42669FFB9FFAAC6F452E1FC85FBF8" blockId="13.[151,1437,150,1113]" pageId="13" pageNumber="214">
<emphasis id="B96FFA7BFFB9FFAAC6F452E1FEB6FC4C" bold="true" box="[199,315,978,1004]" pageId="13" pageNumber="214">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B5DEAFFB9FFAAC45952E0FD72FC4C" authority="Liu &amp; Disney, 2022" authorityName="Liu &amp; Disney" authorityYear="2022" box="[618,767,978,1004]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Pseudacteon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="214" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="reticulatus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B96FFA7BFFB9FFAAC45952E0FD72FC4C" box="[618,767,978,1004]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="214">P. reticulatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B96FFA7BFFB9FFAAC53B52E1FCE9FC4C" bold="true" box="[776,868,978,1004]" pageId="13" pageNumber="214">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A25C4700FFB9FFAAC53B52E1FCE9FC4C" box="[776,868,978,1004]" pageId="13" pageNumber="214" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, it differs from the latter by more frontal setulae, longer second section of wing vein costa, two rounded pieces of sternite VI and no extended membranous apex. It looks also similar to the female of 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B5DEAFFB9FFAAC42B5528FC0EFB94" authority="Michailovskaya, 2000" authorityName="Disney et Michailovskaya" authorityYear="1995" box="[536,899,1050,1076]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Pseudacteon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="214" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pullum">
<emphasis id="B96FFA7BFFB9FFAAC42B5528FD0CFB94" box="[536,641,1050,1076]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="214">P. pullum</emphasis>
Michailovskaya, 2000
</taxonomicName>
, it differs from the latter by narrower abdominal tergite VI, oval sternite VI and smaller vein costal ratio.
</paragraph>
